    <description>
        <p>ChessX is an Open Source chess database. With ChessX you can operate on your collection of chess games in many ways:
browse, edit, add, organize, analyze, etc.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Load and save PGN files</li>
            <li>Work with multiple databases simultaneously</li>
            <li>Browse games, including variations</li>
            <li>Enter moves, variations, comments</li>
            <li>Play games in training mode or play out games against an engine</li>
            <li>Setup board, copy/paste FEN, merge games</li>
            <li>Lint tools to catch performance, usability, version compatibility, and other problems.</li>
            <li>Display opening tree for current position</li>
            <li>Analyze using UCI and Winboard/Xboard Chess engines</li>
            <li>Observe and play games on FICS</li>
        </ul>
    </description>
